{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780736536988,"sessionID":"ses_163d5466cffeJfZ1lzw3MIVtCp","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_15af316787d343fcbafaca7f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-config.json"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-config.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"topic\": \"Can the system-spec-kit memory MCP (mk-spec-memory, 37 tools) be replaced by a CLI with ZERO feature loss? Evaluate three architectures — (a) pure per-invocation CLI, (b) CLI front-end over the existing daemon/IPC socket (kill only the MCP protocol layer), (c) hybrid CLI that auto-spawns the daemon on demand — scoring each against the zero-feature-loss bar across 5 key questions: KQ1 parity matrix for all 37 tools with a CLI equivalent per tool (prior art: generate-context.js already does memory_save; ~11 maintenance CLIs under scripts/dist/memory/); KQ2 daemon-dependency audit (warm embedder, file-watcher reindex, async retry queue/enrichment, RSS watchdog, single-writer serialization, warm session briefs — what dies per architecture); KQ3 MCP-only affordances and replacements (tool-schema auto-discovery, runtime permissioning, Zod boundary validation, -32001 retryable plus session-proxy replay semantics); KQ4 integration-surface migration (runtime hooks for Claude/OpenCode/Codex/Copilot calling session_bootstrap and memory_context, agents allowed-tools, /doctor flows, deep-loop allowed-tools); KQ5 comparison of a/b/c with effort estimates, risk register, go/no-go recommendation. Evidence: a mid-session MCP disconnect left Claude Code unable to reconnect while a CLI re-bridges per call; the launcher/IPC layer already speaks JSON-RPC over daemon-ipc.sock.\",\n3:   \"maxIterations\": 5,\n4:   \"convergenceThreshold\": 0,\n5:   \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n6:   \"maxDurationMinutes\": 240,\n7:   \"specFolder\": \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\",\n8:   \"resource_map_present\": false,\n9:   \"resource_map\": { \"emit\": true },\n10:   \"createdAt\": \"2026-06-06T08:50:55Z\",\n11:   \"status\": \"initialized\",\n12:   \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n13:   \"lineage\": {\n14:     \"sessionId\": \"dr-20260606T105055-fanout028\",\n15:     \"parentSessionId\": null,\n16:     \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n17:     \"generation\": 1,\n18:     \"continuedFromRun\": null\n19:   },\n20:   \"fanout\": {\n21:     \"executors\": [\n22:       { \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\", \"model\": \"deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro\", \"reasoningEffort\": \"high\", \"label\": \"deepseek\", \"count\": 1, \"iterations\": 5 },\n23:       { \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\", \"model\": \"minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3\", \"reasoningEffort\": \"high\", \"label\": \"minimax\", \"count\": 1, \"iterations\": 5, \"timeoutSeconds\": 1500 },\n24:       { \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\", \"model\": \"xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro\", \"reasoningEffort\": \"high\", \"label\": \"mimo\", \"count\": 1, \"iterations\": 5 }\n25:     ],\n26:     \"concurrency\": 2\n27:   }\n28: }\n\n(End of file - total 28 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"topic\": \"Can the system-spec-kit memory MCP (mk-spec-memory, 37 tools) be replaced by a CLI with ZERO feature loss? Evaluate three architectures — (a) pure per-invocation CLI, (b) CLI front-end over the existing daemon/IPC socket (kill only the MCP protocol layer), (c) hybrid CLI that auto-spawns the daemon on demand — scoring each against the zero-feature-loss bar across 5 key questions: KQ1 parity matrix for all 37 tools with a CLI equivalent per tool (prior art: generate-context.js already does memory_save; ~11 maintenance CLIs under scripts/dist/memory/); KQ2 daemon-dependency audit (warm embedder, file-watcher reindex, async retry queue/enrichment, RSS watchdog, single-writer serialization, warm session briefs — what dies per architecture); KQ3 MCP-only affordances and replacements (tool-schema auto-discovery, runtime permissioning, Zod boundary validation, -32001 retryable plus session-proxy replay semantics); KQ4 integration-surface migration (runtime hooks for Claude/OpenCode/Codex/Copilot calling session_bootstrap and memory_context, agents allowed-tools, /doctor flows, deep-loop allowed-tools); KQ5 comparison of a/b/c with effort estimates, risk register, go/no-go recommendation. Evidence: a mid-session MCP disconnect left Claude Code unable to reconnect while a CLI re-bridges per call; the launcher/IPC layer already speaks JSON-RPC over daemon-ipc.sock.\",\n  \"maxIterations\": 5,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0,\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n  \"maxDurationMinutes\": 240,\n  \"specFolder\": \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\",\n  \"resource_map_present\": false,\n  \"resource_map\": { \"emit\": true },\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-06-06T08:50:55Z\",\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n  \"lineage\": {\n    \"sessionId\": \"dr-20260606T105055-fanout028\",\n    \"parentSessionId\": null,\n    \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n    \"generation\": 1,\n    \"continuedFromRun\": null\n  },\n  \"fanout\": {","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-config.json","text":"{\n  \"topic\": \"Can the system-spec-kit memory MCP (mk-spec-memory, 37 tools) be replaced by a CLI with ZERO feature loss? Evaluate three architectures — (a) pure per-invocation CLI, (b) CLI front-end over the existing daemon/IPC socket (kill only the MCP protocol layer), (c) hybrid CLI that auto-spawns the daemon on demand — scoring each against the zero-feature-loss bar across 5 key questions: KQ1 parity matrix for all 37 tools with a CLI equivalent per tool (prior art: generate-context.js already does memory_save; ~11 maintenance CLIs under scripts/dist/memory/); KQ2 daemon-dependency audit (warm embedder, file-watcher reindex, async retry queue/enrichment, RSS watchdog, single-writer serialization, warm session briefs — what dies per architecture); KQ3 MCP-only affordances and replacements (tool-schema auto-discovery, runtime permissioning, Zod boundary validation, -32001 retryable plus session-proxy replay semantics); KQ4 integration-surface migration (runtime hooks for Claude/OpenCode/Codex/Copilot calling session_bootstrap and memory_context, agents allowed-tools, /doctor flows, deep-loop allowed-tools); KQ5 comparison of a/b/c with effort estimates, risk register, go/no-go recommendation. Evidence: a mid-session MCP disconnect left Claude Code unable to reconnect while a CLI re-bridges per call; the launcher/IPC layer already speaks JSON-RPC over daemon-ipc.sock.\",\n  \"maxIterations\": 5,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0,\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n  \"maxDurationMinutes\": 240,\n  \"specFolder\": \".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\",\n  \"resource_map_present\": false,\n  \"resource_map\": { \"emit\": true },\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-06-06T08:50:55Z\",\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n  \"lineage\": {\n    \"sessionId\": \"dr-20260606T105055-fanout028\",\n    \"parentSessionId\": null,\n    \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n    \"generation\": 1,\n    \"continuedFromRun\": null\n  },\n  \"fanout\": {\n    \"executors\": [\n      { \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\", \"model\": \"deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro\", \"reasoningEffort\": \"high\", \"label\": \"deepseek\", \"count\": 1, \"iterations\": 5 },\n      { \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\", \"model\": \"minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3\", \"reasoningEffort\": \"high\", \"label\": \"minimax\", \"count\": 1, \"iterations\": 5, \"timeoutSeconds\": 1500 },\n      { \"kind\": \"cli-opencode\", \"model\": \"xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro\", \"reasoningEffort\": \"high\", \"label\": \"mimo\", \"count\": 1, \"iterations\": 5 }\n    ],\n    \"concurrency\": 2\n  }\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":28,"totalLines":28,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-config.json","time":{"start":1780736536971,"end":1780736536987}},"id":"prt_e9c2b31860013jsYztNlF5Ygyk","sessionID":"ses_163d5466cffeJfZ1lzw3MIVtCp","messageID":"msg_e9c2b2567001Cg1uz3X3Uf8a30"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780736537619,"sessionID":"ses_163d5466cffeJfZ1lzw3MIVtCp","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_7312633b9c5b4c4f8b39a074","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-strategy.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research Strategy\n2: \n3: ## Topic\n4: \n5: Can the system-spec-kit memory MCP (mk-spec-memory, 37 tools) be replaced by a CLI with ZERO feature loss? Evaluate three architectures — (a) pure per-invocation CLI, (b) CLI front-end over the existing daemon/IPC socket (kill only the MCP protocol layer), (c) hybrid CLI that auto-spawns the daemon on demand — scoring each against the zero-feature-loss bar.\n6: \n7: ## Key Questions\n8: \n9: - [ ] KQ1: What is the CLI equivalent for each of the 37 MCP tools (full parity matrix)? Prior art: `generate-context.js` already performs memory_save; ~11 maintenance CLIs exist under `scripts/dist/memory/`.\n10: - [ ] KQ2: Which features depend on a long-lived daemon (warm embedder, file-watcher reindex, async retry queue/enrichment, RSS watchdog, single-writer serialization, warm session briefs), and what dies under each architecture?\n11: - [ ] KQ3: Which affordances exist ONLY because of the MCP protocol (tool-schema auto-discovery, runtime permissioning, Zod boundary validation, -32001 retryable + session-proxy replay), and what are the concrete CLI replacements?\n12: - [ ] KQ4: What does migrating every current MCP caller entail (runtime hooks for Claude/OpenCode/Codex/Copilot calling session_bootstrap/memory_context, agents' allowed-tools, /doctor flows, deep-loop allowed-tools)?\n13: - [ ] KQ5: How do architectures a/b/c compare on the zero-feature-loss bar, effort, and risk — and what is the go/no-go recommendation?\n14: \n15: ## Known Context\n16: \n17: Verified facts available at init (from pre-run exploration of this repo; lanes should re-verify citations independently):\n18: - The MCP server registers 37 tools across 5 registry files under `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tools/` (memory 16, context 1, causal 4, checkpoint 4, lifecycle 12).\n19: - The launcher/daemon layer (`.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` + `lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs` + `lib/launcher-session-proxy.cjs`) already speaks JSON-RPC over a unix socket (`daemon-ipc.sock`); the MCP-protocol-specific surface is the stdio transport + tool schemas + session-proxy replay classification.\n20: - Daemon-resident services: local-first embedding cascade (ollama → hf-local → OpenAI → Voyage) with warm model server, chokidar file-watcher, async embedding retry queue, RSS watchdog with in-place recycle, owner-lease single-writer model.\n21: - CLI prior art: `scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js` (canonical save), plus reindex/cleanup/validate/backfill/rank maintenance CLIs.\n22: - Operational evidence FOR de-MCP-ing: 2026-06-06 mid-session MCP disconnect (owner session closed; bridged secondary rode the ~41s reattach ladder, gave up, and Claude Code never reconnects MCP mid-session — 45 tools lost for the session). A per-call CLI would have re-bridged.\n23: - Evidence AGAINST / costs: MCP gives agents automatic tool discovery + schemas + per-tool permission gating; hooks and agents across 4 runtimes currently call MCP tools directly.\n24: \n25: ## Negative Knowledge (ruled out)\n26: \n27: - (none yet)\n28: \n29: ## Next Focus\n30: \n31: Start with KQ1 (parity matrix) and KQ2 (daemon-dependency audit) — they anchor every other question.\n32: \n33: ## Parameters\n34: \n35: - Max iterations: 5 (per lane, terminal cap)\n36: - Convergence threshold: 0 (forced full iteration budget; legal early stop only via all-questions-answered)\n\n(End of file - total 36 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research Strategy\n\n## Topic\n\nCan the system-spec-kit memory MCP (mk-spec-memory, 37 tools) be replaced by a CLI with ZERO feature loss? Evaluate three architectures — (a) pure per-invocation CLI, (b) CLI front-end over the existing daemon/IPC socket (kill only the MCP protocol layer), (c) hybrid CLI that auto-spawns the daemon on demand — scoring each against the zero-feature-loss bar.\n\n## Key Questions\n\n- [ ] KQ1: What is the CLI equivalent for each of the 37 MCP tools (full parity matrix)? Prior art: `generate-context.js` already performs memory_save; ~11 maintenance CLIs exist under `scripts/dist/memory/`.\n- [ ] KQ2: Which features depend on a long-lived daemon (warm embedder, file-watcher reindex, async retry queue/enrichment, RSS watchdog, single-writer serialization, warm session briefs), and what dies under each architecture?\n- [ ] KQ3: Which affordances exist ONLY because of the MCP protocol (tool-schema auto-discovery, runtime permissioning, Zod boundary validation, -32001 retryable + session-proxy replay), and what are the concrete CLI replacements?\n- [ ] KQ4: What does migrating every current MCP caller entail (runtime hooks for Claude/OpenCode/Codex/Copilot calling session_bootstrap/memory_context, agents' allowed-tools, /doctor flows, deep-loop allowed-tools)?\n- [ ] KQ5: How do architectures a/b/c compare on the zero-feature-loss bar, effort, and risk — and what is the go/no-go recommendation?\n\n## Known Context\n\nVerified facts available at init (from pre-run exploration of this repo; lanes should re-verify citations independently):\n- The MCP server registers 37 tools across 5 registry files under `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tools/` (memory 16, context 1, causal 4, checkpoint 4, lifecycle 12).\n- The launcher/daemon layer (`.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` + `lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs` + `lib/launcher-session-proxy.cjs`) already speaks JSON-RPC over a unix socket (`daemon-ipc.sock`); the MCP-protocol-specific surface is the stdio transport + tool schemas + session-proxy replay classification.\n- Daemon-resident services: local-first embedding cascade (ollama → hf-local → OpenAI → Voyage) with warm model server, chokidar file-watcher, async embedding retry queue, RSS watchdog with in-place recycle, owner-lease single-writer model.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"# Deep Research Strategy\n\n## Topic\n\nCan the system-spec-kit memory MCP (mk-spec-memory, 37 tools) be replaced by a CLI with ZERO feature loss? Evaluate three architectures — (a) pure per-invocation CLI, (b) CLI front-end over the existing daemon/IPC socket (kill only the MCP protocol layer), (c) hybrid CLI that auto-spawns the daemon on demand — scoring each against the zero-feature-loss bar.\n\n## Key Questions\n\n- [ ] KQ1: What is the CLI equivalent for each of the 37 MCP tools (full parity matrix)? Prior art: `generate-context.js` already performs memory_save; ~11 maintenance CLIs exist under `scripts/dist/memory/`.\n- [ ] KQ2: Which features depend on a long-lived daemon (warm embedder, file-watcher reindex, async retry queue/enrichment, RSS watchdog, single-writer serialization, warm session briefs), and what dies under each architecture?\n- [ ] KQ3: Which affordances exist ONLY because of the MCP protocol (tool-schema auto-discovery, runtime permissioning, Zod boundary validation, -32001 retryable + session-proxy replay), and what are the concrete CLI replacements?\n- [ ] KQ4: What does migrating every current MCP caller entail (runtime hooks for Claude/OpenCode/Codex/Copilot calling session_bootstrap/memory_context, agents' allowed-tools, /doctor flows, deep-loop allowed-tools)?\n- [ ] KQ5: How do architectures a/b/c compare on the zero-feature-loss bar, effort, and risk — and what is the go/no-go recommendation?\n\n## Known Context\n\nVerified facts available at init (from pre-run exploration of this repo; lanes should re-verify citations independently):\n- The MCP server registers 37 tools across 5 registry files under `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tools/` (memory 16, context 1, causal 4, checkpoint 4, lifecycle 12).\n- The launcher/daemon layer (`.opencode/bin/mk-spec-memory-launcher.cjs` + `lib/launcher-ipc-bridge.cjs` + `lib/launcher-session-proxy.cjs`) already speaks JSON-RPC over a unix socket (`daemon-ipc.sock`); the MCP-protocol-specific surface is the stdio transport + tool schemas + session-proxy replay classification.\n- Daemon-resident services: local-first embedding cascade (ollama → hf-local → OpenAI → Voyage) with warm model server, chokidar file-watcher, async embedding retry queue, RSS watchdog with in-place recycle, owner-lease single-writer model.\n- CLI prior art: `scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js` (canonical save), plus reindex/cleanup/validate/backfill/rank maintenance CLIs.\n- Operational evidence FOR de-MCP-ing: 2026-06-06 mid-session MCP disconnect (owner session closed; bridged secondary rode the ~41s reattach ladder, gave up, and Claude Code never reconnects MCP mid-session — 45 tools lost for the session). A per-call CLI would have re-bridged.\n- Evidence AGAINST / costs: MCP gives agents automatic tool discovery + schemas + per-tool permission gating; hooks and agents across 4 runtimes currently call MCP tools directly.\n\n## Negative Knowledge (ruled out)\n\n- (none yet)\n\n## Next Focus\n\nStart with KQ1 (parity matrix) and KQ2 (daemon-dependency audit) — they anchor every other question.\n\n## Parameters\n\n- Max iterations: 5 (per lane, terminal cap)\n- Convergence threshold: 0 (forced full iteration budget; legal early stop only via all-questions-answered)","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":36,"totalLines":36,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1780736537611,"end":1780736537617}},"id":"prt_e9c2b3407001QABs8YuKNR6Jl0","sessionID":"ses_163d5466cffeJfZ1lzw3MIVtCp","messageID":"msg_e9c2b2567001Cg1uz3X3Uf8a30"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780736538159,"sessionID":"ses_163d5466cffeJfZ1lzw3MIVtCp","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_d2918dc0a6ea476a862ecc7c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-state.jsonl"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-state.jsonl</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"Can the system-spec-kit memory MCP (mk-spec-memory, 37 tools) be replaced by a CLI with ZERO feature loss? Evaluate three architectures against the zero-feature-loss bar across 5 key questions (parity matrix, daemon-dependency audit, MCP-only affordances, integration-surface migration, architecture comparison with go/no-go).\",\"maxIterations\":5,\"convergenceThreshold\":0,\"resource_map_present\":false,\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":true},\"createdAt\":\"2026-06-06T08:50:55Z\",\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\"}\n2: {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"fanout_mode\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"lineages\":[\"deepseek\",\"minimax\",\"mimo\"],\"concurrency\":2,\"perLineageIterations\":5,\"sessionId\":\"dr-20260606T105055-fanout028\",\"generation\":1,\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-06T08:50:55Z\"}\n\n(End of file - total 2 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"Can the system-spec-kit memory MCP (mk-spec-memory, 37 tools) be replaced by a CLI with ZERO feature loss? Evaluate three architectures against the zero-feature-loss bar across 5 key questions (parity matrix, daemon-dependency audit, MCP-only affordances, integration-surface migration, architecture comparison with go/no-go).\",\"maxIterations\":5,\"convergenceThreshold\":0,\"resource_map_present\":false,\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":true},\"createdAt\":\"2026-06-06T08:50:55Z\",\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\"}\n{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"fanout_mode\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"lineages\":[\"deepseek\",\"minimax\",\"mimo\"],\"concurrency\":2,\"perLineageIterations\":5,\"sessionId\":\"dr-20260606T105055-fanout028\",\"generation\":1,\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-06T08:50:55Z\"}","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-state.jsonl","text":"{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"Can the system-spec-kit memory MCP (mk-spec-memory, 37 tools) be replaced by a CLI with ZERO feature loss? Evaluate three architectures against the zero-feature-loss bar across 5 key questions (parity matrix, daemon-dependency audit, MCP-only affordances, integration-surface migration, architecture comparison with go/no-go).\",\"maxIterations\":5,\"convergenceThreshold\":0,\"resource_map_present\":false,\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":true},\"createdAt\":\"2026-06-06T08:50:55Z\",\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility\"}\n{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"fanout_mode\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"lineages\":[\"deepseek\",\"minimax\",\"mimo\"],\"concurrency\":2,\"perLineageIterations\":5,\"sessionId\":\"dr-20260606T105055-fanout028\",\"generation\":1,\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-06T08:50:55Z\"}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":2,"totalLines":2,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/deep-research-state.jsonl","time":{"start":1780736538150,"end":1780736538157}},"id":"prt_e9c2b3622001n246YXvNVMhhop","sessionID":"ses_163d5466cffeJfZ1lzw3MIVtCp","messageID":"msg_e9c2b2567001Cg1uz3X3Uf8a30"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780736538693,"sessionID":"ses_163d5466cffeJfZ1lzw3MIVtCp","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_bbfde8dc3b37429d82bdd666","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages</path>\n<type>directory</type>\n<entries>\ndeepseek/\nmimo/\nminimax/\n\n(3 entries)\n</entries>","metadata":{"preview":"deepseek/\nmimo/\nminimax/","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"directory","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages","entries":["deepseek/","mimo/","minimax/"],"offset":1,"totalEntries":3,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-mcp-cli-feasibility/research/lineages","time":{"start":1780736538688,"end":1780736538691}},"id":"prt_e9c2b383c001dD0m1cKbwDVQNN","sessionID":"ses_163d5466cffeJfZ1lzw3MIVtCp","messageID":"msg_e9c2b2567001Cg1uz3X3Uf8a30"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780736539326,"sessionID":"ses_163d5466cffeJfZ1lzw3MIVtCp","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_973fb62cfdb448598de02cdf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: DEEP-RESEARCH\n2: \n3: # Deep-Research Iteration Prompt Pack\n4: \n5: This prompt pack renders the per-iteration context for the `@deep-research` LEAF agent (native executor) or a CLI executor (e.g. `codex exec`). Tokens use curly-brace syntax and are substituted by `renderPromptPack` before dispatch.\n6: \n7: ## STATE\n8: \n9: {state_summary}\n10: \n11: Research Topic: {research_topic}\n12: Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n13: Focus Area: {next_focus}\n14: Remaining Key Questions: {remaining_questions_list}\n15: Last 3 Iterations Summary: {last_3_summaries}\n16: \n17: ## STATE FILES\n18: \n19: All paths are relative to the repo root.\n20: \n21: - Config: {state_paths_config}\n22: - State Log: {state_paths_state_log}\n23: - Strategy: {state_paths_strategy}\n24: - Registry: {state_paths_registry}\n25: - Write iteration narrative to: {state_paths_iteration_pattern}\n26: - Write per-iteration delta file to: {state_paths_delta_pattern}\n27: \n28: ## CONSTRAINTS\n29: \n30: - You are a LEAF agent. Do NOT dispatch sub-agents.\n31: - Target 3-5 research actions. Max 12 tool calls total.\n32: - Write ALL findings to files. Do not hold in context.\n33: - The workflow reducer owns strategy machine-owned sections, registry, and dashboard synchronization.\n34: - Do not implement fixes during review. Report findings only; implementation is a separate follow-up step.\n35: - When emitting the iteration JSONL record, include an optional `graphEvents` array of `{type, id, label, relation?, source?, target?}` objects representing coverage graph nodes and edges discovered this iteration. Omit the field when no graph events are produced.\n36: \n37: ## OUTPUT CONTRACT\n38: \n39: You MUST produce THREE artifacts per iteration. The YAML-owned post_dispatch_validate step emits a `schema_mismatch` conflict event if any is missing or malformed.\n40: \n41: 1. **Iteration narrative markdown** at `{state_paths_iteration_pattern}` (path is pre-substituted for the current iteration number). Structure: headings for Focus, Actions Taken, Findings, Questions Answered, Questions Remaining, Next Focus.\n42: \n43: 2. **Canonical JSONL iteration record** APPENDED to `{state_paths_state_log}`. The record MUST use `\"type\":\"iteration\"` EXACTLY — NOT `\"iteration_delta\"` or any other variant. The reducer counts records where `type === \"iteration\"` only; other types are silently ignored (the iteration will look incomplete and the reducer may re-run it). Required schema:\n44: \n45: ```json\n46: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":<n>,\"newInfoRatio\":<0..1>,\"status\":\"<string>\",\"focus\":\"<string>\",\"graphEvents\":[/* optional */],\"executor\":{/* workflow-owned for non-native runs */}}\n47: ```\n48: \n49: Append via single-line JSON with newline terminator — for example: `echo '<single-line-json>' >> {state_paths_state_log}`. Do NOT pretty-print. Do NOT print the JSON to stdout only; it MUST land in the state log file.\n50: \n51: For non-native CLI executors, the workflow owns executor provenance. It writes a pre-dispatch sentinel, then patches the first canonical `\"type\":\"iteration\"` record with the `executor` block before `post_dispatch_validate` runs. Do NOT append your own `dispatch_failure` event or a partial fallback record when the executor itself crashes or times out; the workflow emits the typed failure event on that path.\n52: \n53: 3. **Per-iteration delta file** at `{state_paths_delta_pattern}` (path pre-substituted for the current iteration — e.g. `deltas/iter-001.jsonl`). This file holds the structured delta stream for this iteration: one `{\"type\":\"iteration\",...}` record (same content as the state-log append) plus per-event structured records (one per graphEvent, finding, invariant, observation, edge, ruled_out direction). Each record on its own JSON line. The reducer reads the combined state log + delta files to rebuild dashboards and registries after interruption or partial runs.\n54: \n55: Example delta file contents (one iteration):\n56: ```json\n57: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":3,\"newInfoRatio\":0.62,\"status\":\"insight\",\"focus\":\"...\"}\n58: {\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-iter003-001\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"label\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n59: {\"type\":\"invariant\",\"id\":\"inv-iter003-001\",\"label\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n60: {\"type\":\"observation\",\"id\":\"obs-iter003-001\",\"packet\":\"007\",\"classification\":\"real\",\"iteration\":3}\n61: {\"type\":\"edge\",\"id\":\"e-iter003-001\",\"relation\":\"VIOLATES\",\"source\":\"obs-001\",\"target\":\"inv-001\",\"iteration\":3}\n62: {\"type\":\"ruled_out\",\"direction\":\"...\",\"reason\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n63: ```\n64: \n65: All three artifacts are REQUIRED. The post_dispatch_validate step fails the iteration if any artifact is missing, malformed, or if the state-log append uses the wrong record type (`iteration_delta` etc.).\n\n(End of file - total 65 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"DEEP-RESEARCH\n\n# Deep-Research Iteration Prompt Pack\n\nThis prompt pack renders the per-iteration context for the `@deep-research` LEAF agent (native executor) or a CLI executor (e.g. `codex exec`). Tokens use curly-brace syntax and are substituted by `renderPromptPack` before dispatch.\n\n## STATE\n\n{state_summary}\n\nResearch Topic: {research_topic}\nIteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\nFocus Area: {next_focus}\nRemaining Key Questions: {remaining_questions_list}\nLast 3 Iterations Summary: {last_3_summaries}\n\n## STATE FILES\n\nAll paths are relative to the repo root.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl","text":"DEEP-RESEARCH\n\n# Deep-Research Iteration Prompt Pack\n\nThis prompt pack renders the per-iteration context for the `@deep-research` LEAF agent (native executor) or a CLI executor (e.g. `codex exec`). Tokens use curly-brace syntax and are substituted by `renderPromptPack` before dispatch.\n\n## STATE\n\n{state_summary}\n\nResearch Topic: {research_topic}\nIteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\nFocus Area: {next_focus}\nRemaining Key Questions: {remaining_questions_list}\nLast 3 Iterations Summary: {last_3_summaries}\n\n## STATE FILES\n\nAll paths are relative to the repo root.\n\n- Config: {state_paths_config}\n- State Log: {state_paths_state_log}\n- Strategy: {state_paths_strategy}\n- Registry: {state_paths_registry}\n- Write iteration narrative to: {state_paths_iteration_pattern}\n- Write per-iteration delta file to: {state_paths_delta_pattern}\n\n## CONSTRAINTS\n\n- You are a LEAF agent. Do NOT dispatch sub-agents.\n- Target 3-5 research actions. Max 12 tool calls total.\n- Write ALL findings to files. Do not hold in context.\n- The workflow reducer owns strategy machine-owned sections, registry, and dashboard synchronization.\n- Do not implement fixes during review. Report findings only; implementation is a separate follow-up step.\n- When emitting the iteration JSONL record, include an optional `graphEvents` array of `{type, id, label, relation?, source?, target?}` objects representing coverage graph nodes and edges discovered this iteration. Omit the field when no graph events are produced.\n\n## OUTPUT CONTRACT\n\nYou MUST produce THREE artifacts per iteration. The YAML-owned post_dispatch_validate step emits a `schema_mismatch` conflict event if any is missing or malformed.\n\n1. **Iteration narrative markdown** at `{state_paths_iteration_pattern}` (path is pre-substituted for the current iteration number). Structure: headings for Focus, Actions Taken, Findings, Questions Answered, Questions Remaining, Next Focus.\n\n2. **Canonical JSONL iteration record** APPENDED to `{state_paths_state_log}`. The record MUST use `\"type\":\"iteration\"` EXACTLY — NOT `\"iteration_delta\"` or any other variant. The reducer counts records where `type === \"iteration\"` only; other types are silently ignored (the iteration will look incomplete and the reducer may re-run it). Required schema:\n\n```json\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":<n>,\"newInfoRatio\":<0..1>,\"status\":\"<string>\",\"focus\":\"<string>\",\"graphEvents\":[/* optional */],\"executor\":{/* workflow-owned for non-native runs */}}\n```\n\nAppend via single-line JSON with newline terminator — for example: `echo '<single-line-json>' >> {state_paths_state_log}`. Do NOT pretty-print. Do NOT print the JSON to stdout only; it MUST land in the state log file.\n\nFor non-native CLI executors, the workflow owns executor provenance. It writes a pre-dispatch sentinel, then patches the first canonical `\"type\":\"iteration\"` record with the `executor` block before `post_dispatch_validate` runs. Do NOT append your own `dispatch_failure` event or a partial fallback record when the executor itself crashes or times out; the workflow emits the typed failure event on that path.\n\n3. **Per-iteration delta file** at `{state_paths_delta_pattern}` (path pre-substituted for the current iteration — e.g. `deltas/iter-001.jsonl`). This file holds the structured delta stream for this iteration: one `{\"type\":\"iteration\",...}` record (same content as the state-log append) plus per-event structured records (one per graphEvent, finding, invariant, observation, edge, ruled_out direction). Each record on its own JSON line. The reducer reads the combined state log + delta files to rebuild dashboards and registries after interruption or partial runs.\n\nExample delta file contents (one iteration):\n```json\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":3,\"newInfoRatio\":0.62,\"status\":\"insight\",\"focus\":\"...\"}\n{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f-iter003-001\",\"severity\":\"P1\",\"label\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n{\"type\":\"invariant\",\"id\":\"inv-iter003-001\",\"label\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n{\"type\":\"observation\",\"id\":\"obs-iter003-001\",\"packet\":\"007\",\"classification\":\"real\",\"iteration\":3}\n{\"type\":\"edge\",\"id\":\"e-iter003-001\",\"relation\":\"VIOLATES\",\"source\":\"obs-001\",\"target\":\"inv-001\",\"iteration\":3}\n{\"type\":\"ruled_out\",\"direction\":\"...\",\"reason\":\"...\",\"iteration\":3}\n```\n\nAll three artifacts are REQUIRED. The post_dispatch_validate step fails the iteration if any artifact is missing, malformed, or if the state-log append uses the wrong record type (`iteration_delta` etc.).","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":65,"totalLines":65,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl","time":{"start":1780736539316,"end":1780736539324}},"id":"prt_e9c2b3aa9001n532o6dmdjwAKC","sessionID":"ses_163d5466cffeJfZ1lzw3MIVtCp","messageID":"msg_e9c2b2567001Cg1uz3X3Uf8a30"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780736539803,"sessionID":"ses_163d5466cffeJfZ1lzw3MIVtCp","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ec7c3207b9f74c479fd368d3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Strategy Template\n3: description: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n7: \n8: Runtime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n9: \n10: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n11: \n12: ### Purpose\n13: \n14: Serves as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep research session. Records what to investigate, what worked, what failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n15: \n16: ### Usage\n17: \n18: - **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{spec_folder}/research/deep-research-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Key Questions, Known Context, and Research Boundaries from config and memory context.\n19: - **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, writes iteration evidence, and the reducer refreshes What Worked/Failed, answered questions, ruled-out directions, and Next Focus.\n20: - **Mutability:** Mutable — analyst-owned sections remain stable, while machine-owned sections are rewritten by the reducer after each iteration.\n21: - **Protection:** Shared state with explicit ownership boundaries. Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n22: \n23: ---\n24: \n25: ## 2. TOPIC\n26: [Research topic from config -- set during initialization]\n27: \n28: ---\n29: \n30: ## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n31: - [ ] [Question 1 -- identified during initialization or iteration 1]\n32: - [ ] [Question 2]\n33: - [ ] [Question 3]\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ## 4. NON-GOALS\n38: [What this research session is NOT trying to answer -- populated during initialization]\n39: \n40: ---\n41: \n42: ## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n43: [Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n48: [None yet -- populated as iterations answer questions]\n49: \n50: ---\n51: \n52: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n53: ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n54: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n55: - [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n60: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n61: - [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n66: [Populated when an approach has been tried from multiple angles without success]\n67: \n68: ### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n69: - What was tried: [specific approaches attempted]\n70: - Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n71: - Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n72: \n73: ### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n74: - What worked: [successful approaches in this category]\n75: - Prefer for: [related questions where this category may help]\n76: \n77: ---\n78: \n79: ## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n80: [Approaches that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n81: - [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n82: \n83: ---\n84: \n85: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n86: [Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration]\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n91: ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n92: [Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n93: \n94: ---\n95: \n96: ## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n97: - Max iterations: [from config]\n98: - Convergence threshold: [from config]\n99: - Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n100: - Progressive synthesis: true (default)\n101: - research/research.md ownership: workflow-owned canonical synthesis output\n102: - Lifecycle branches: `resume`, `restart` (live); `fork`, `completed-continue` (deferred, not runtime-wired)\n103: - Machine-owned sections: reducer controls Sections 3, 6, 7-11\n104: - Canonical pause sentinel: `research/.deep-research-pause`\n105: - Capability matrix: `.opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json`\n106: - Capability matrix doc: `.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md`\n107: - Capability resolver: `.opencode/skills/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs`\n108: - Current generation: [from config.lineage.generation]\n109: - Started: [timestamp]\n\n(End of file - total 109 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nServes as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep research session. Records what to investigate, what worked, what failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n\n### Usage\n\n- **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{spec_folder}/research/deep-research-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Key Questions, Known Context, and Research Boundaries from config and memory context.\n- **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, writes iteration evidence, and the reducer refreshes What Worked/Failed, answered questions, ruled-out directions, and Next Focus.\n- **Mutability:** Mutable — analyst-owned sections remain stable, while machine-owned sections are rewritten by the reducer after each iteration.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nServes as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep research session. Records what to investigate, what worked, what failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n\n### Usage\n\n- **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{spec_folder}/research/deep-research-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Key Questions, Known Context, and Research Boundaries from config and memory context.\n- **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, writes iteration evidence, and the reducer refreshes What Worked/Failed, answered questions, ruled-out directions, and Next Focus.\n- **Mutability:** Mutable — analyst-owned sections remain stable, while machine-owned sections are rewritten by the reducer after each iteration.\n- **Protection:** Shared state with explicit ownership boundaries. Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n\n---\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n[Research topic from config -- set during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n- [ ] [Question 1 -- identified during initialization or iteration 1]\n- [ ] [Question 2]\n- [ ] [Question 3]\n\n---\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n[What this research session is NOT trying to answer -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n[Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n[None yet -- populated as iterations answer questions]\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n## 7. WHAT WORKED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n\n---\n\n## 8. WHAT FAILED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n\n---\n\n## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n[Populated when an approach has been tried from multiple angles without success]\n\n### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n- What was tried: [specific approaches attempted]\n- Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n- Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n\n### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n- What worked: [successful approaches in this category]\n- Prefer for: [related questions where this category may help]\n\n---\n\n## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n[Approaches that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n- [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n\n---\n\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n[Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration]\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n[Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n\n---\n\n## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n- Max iterations: [from config]\n- Convergence threshold: [from config]\n- Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n- Progressive synthesis: true (default)\n- research/research.md ownership: workflow-owned canonical synthesis output\n- Lifecycle branches: `resume`, `restart` (live); `fork`, `completed-continue` (deferred, not runtime-wired)\n- Machine-owned sections: reducer controls Sections 3, 6, 7-11\n- Canonical pause sentinel: `research/.deep-research-pause`\n- Capability matrix: `.opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json`\n- Capability matrix doc: `.opencode/skills/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md`\n- Capability resolver: `.opencode/skills/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs`\n- Current generation: [from config.lineage.generation]\n- Started: [timestamp]","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":109,"totalLines":109,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md","time":{"start":1780736539796,"end":1780736539800}},"id":"prt_e9c2b3c90001omxX7xpdZjtqat","sessionID":"ses_163d5466cffeJfZ1lzw3MIVtCp","messageID":"msg_e9c2b2567001Cg1uz3X3Uf8a30"}}
